{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#3224: types: Component cannot be rendered with JSX",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:28:00.691534+00:00",
  "text": "types: Component cannot be rendered with JSX\n\n### Version\r\n3.0.5\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[https://codesandbox.io/s/boring-babbage-lgpd9?file=/src/main.tsx](https://codesandbox.io/s/boring-babbage-lgpd9?file=/src/main.tsx)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nTry to compile `declare const Foo: Component; return <Foo />`\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nNo errors. `<Bar />` should complain about a missing `id` prop. \r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n`JSX element type 'Foo' does not have any construct or call signatures`\r\n\r\n---\r\nThis was broken with `h(Foo)` too until #3219\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
